## Purpose

Use this template when a WA3 renderer needs a compact mobile-first app shell
with a premium future-tech HMI mood: simulated device viewport, glowing nebula
background, frosted quartz cards, bottom tab navigation, metric/story/resource
pages, holographic modal confirmations, progress affordances, and short
nonblocking toast feedback.

## Safety Boundary

- Display guidance only; never execute source code from the referenced design.
- Do not copy backend targets, providers, policies, permissions, secrets, true
  action ids, true button labels, source asset references, fonts, visual
  identity assets, or executable implementation files.
- Treat words such as "secure", "encrypted", "biometric", "vault", and
  "verified" as visual tone unless a verified WA3 contract/runtime state says
  otherwise.
- Long-press, scan, fingerprint, call, mail, download, and transmission motifs
  are interaction shapes only. They must not imply authentication, delivery,
  local storage, network transfer, or permission state.
- Every real interaction must map back to a verified operable WA3 contract and
  pass through `wa3-core`.

