## Component Roles

```json
{
  "device_frame": {
    "shape": "centered rounded mobile viewport with dark metal rim and hidden overflow",
    "desktop": "may appear as a device preview; avoid using the frame when the app is already inside a real mobile container",
    "mobile": "remove decorative outer rim and use real safe areas"
  },
  "status_island": {
    "shape": "small black pill at top center with tiny sensor dots",
    "notes": "pure decoration; carries no device, camera, identity, or permission state"
  },
  "ambient_background": {
    "shape": "full-bleed deep-space gradient with blurred cyan/purple light fields",
    "behavior": "background motion must be subtle and optional"
  },
  "compact_title_stack": {
    "shape": "tiny mono uppercase eyebrow above bold short title with a small pulsing status dot",
    "notes": "status dot only reflects verified runtime state when bound to real state"
  },
  "round_icon_button": {
    "shape": "36px circular glass button with icon centered, cyan hover/focus ring, active scale feedback",
    "states": ["default", "hover", "focus", "pressed", "disabled"],
    "notes": "icon buttons map to declared actions only at render time"
  },
  "page_section_header": {
    "shape": "compact row with numbered section label left and mono status chip right",
    "body": "short muted paragraph; keep to two or three lines on mobile"
  },
  "quartz_product_card": {
    "shape": "large frosted glass card with icon cell, mono index, bold title, short body, and three compact spec cells",
    "states": ["default", "hover_or_pressed", "loading"],
    "notes": "spec values are plain display data unless backed by verified data provenance"
  },
  "carousel_dots": {
    "shape": "tiny pill indicators; active item expands horizontally",
    "behavior": "switches display-only page/item state unless wired to a declared WA3 action"
  },
  "metric_card": {
    "shape": "glass card with label, large numeric value, icon cell, and tiny legend row",
    "notes": "animated counters should settle to verified values; never fabricate live metrics"
  },
  "horizontal_case_card": {
    "shape": "fixed-width snap card with small mono tag, icon, title, concise body, and bottom metadata row",
    "mobile": "horizontal scroll with hidden scrollbar and snap points"
  },
  "timeline": {
    "shape": "vertical glowing spine with small circular nodes and compact milestone cards",
    "mobile": "single-column scroll area with current item highlighted"
  },
  "resource_row": {
    "shape": "glass list row with file/type icon cell, title/meta stack, and square icon action button",
    "states": ["available", "disabled", "preparing"],
    "notes": "download or open behavior must map to a declared action and runtime confirmation when required"
  },
  "bottom_tab_nav": {
    "shape": "fixed bottom navigation with four icon+label tabs and translucent sliding active indicator",
    "behavior": "only one tab page visible; active color is cyan, inactive is muted slate"
  },
  "hmi_modal": {
    "shape": "centered dark glass panel over blurred scrim with cyan border glow, corner brackets, and optional scanline",
    "use_for": ["confirmation", "contact", "detail", "form"],
    "notes": "modal cannot replace WA3 confirmation, permission checks, or trust state"
  },
  "hmi_form_control": {
    "shape": "dark compact input with mono uppercase label, soft border, cyan focus ring, and small text",
    "states": ["default", "focus", "invalid", "disabled"]
  },
  "long_press_progress_control": {
    "shape": "round icon button inside circular progress ring with hold-to-complete feedback",
    "behavior": "visual confirmation affordance only; completion reports intent to runtime",
    "notes": "does not authenticate the user unless the verified runtime provides real authentication"
  },
  "holographic_toast": {
    "shape": "bottom floating HMI panel with icon cell, mono heading, short description, and cyan corner accents",
    "duration": "short and nonblocking; persistent errors become inline panels"
  },
  "action_role_slots": {
    "primary_submit": {
      "match": "verified WA3 action that submits the current modal/form or starts the main mobile flow",
      "component": "hmi_modal primary button or long_press_progress_control",
      "style": "small cyan glass button or circular progress button with neon-cyan border, compact label, and fixed height",
      "fallback": "derive a cyan glass primary control from neon_cyan, surface_dark, and control radius tokens; do not create a feature"
    },
    "secondary_action": {
      "match": "verified secondary action, cancel, close, back, or low-risk helper action",
      "component": "hmi_modal secondary button",
      "style": "small muted glass button with soft border and slate text; active scale feedback allowed"
    },
    "compact_icon_action": {
      "match": "verified quick action, resource-row action, or repeated compact control",
      "component": "round_icon_button or resource_row square icon action",
      "style": "36px circular or square glass icon button with centered icon, cyan hover/focus ring, and fixed size"
    },
    "navigation_or_filter": {
      "match": "display navigation, tab, carousel switcher, search, or filter control",
      "component": "bottom_tab_nav, carousel_dots, or compact header filter",
      "style": "cyan active state, muted slate inactive state, sliding/pill indicator when space allows"
    },
    "destructive_confirm": {
      "match": "verified destructive, irreversible, or high-risk mutating action that already requires confirmation",
      "component": "hmi_modal confirmation button or long_press_progress_control",
      "style": "cyan HMI confirmation surface with visible target summary; optional hold progress is extra visual friction",
      "notes": "visual treatment only; confirmation and target still come from wa3-core"
    }
  }
}
```

## WA3 Block Mapping

```json
{
  "ㄆㄤ": "render as tab_page_stack or modal form surface when paired with verified submit/search actions",
  "ㄗㄞ": "render as quartz_product_card, horizontal_case_card, resource_row, timeline item, or metric_card",
  "ㄔㄠ": "render as hmi_modal form or compact inline form with long_press_progress_control only when the verified contract allows confirmation",
  "ㄙㄞ": "render as compact header filter, tab selector, carousel switcher, or resource-list filter",
  "ㄉㄟ": "render as metric_card, spec cells, resource detail modal, or timeline detail panel",
  "ㄇㄢ": "render as safe compact text inside page_section_header, card body, toast, or modal body"
}
```

## Interaction Guidance

- Keep the app shell compact: repeated controls need stable width/height so tab
  labels, icons, counters, and progress rings do not resize the layout.
- Use bottom tabs for major modes and card/row interactions for local
  navigation. A tab switch is display navigation unless bound to a verified
  WA3 action.
- Prefer icons from the host renderer's allowed icon system. If none exists,
  use initials or simple CSS shapes instead of copying icon fonts.
- Place mutating-operation confirmation in the HMI modal or long-press control
  only as an additional visual affordance; `wa3-core` still owns confirmation.
- Keep secure/biometric/download/call/mail wording generic unless the verified
  contract supplies the actual action and runtime trust state.
- Disable nebula movement, scanlines, particles, floating cards, animated
  counters, and circular hold progress under reduced motion.
- Toasts are for feedback only. Errors that require user action should become
  visible inline panels inside the relevant page or modal.
- Decorative effects such as scanlines, particles, glow brackets, device frames,
  and scrims must not intercept pointer or keyboard activation. Put actionable
  controls above decorative layers and give noninteractive layers no hit target.
- Forms and confirmation modals must account for the bottom tab safe area. The
  primary submit/confirm control must be visible and reachable without being
  covered by the tab bar, device frame, toast, or modal decoration.
- If a renderer offers mock persistence for preview, such as local storage or an
  in-memory provider, label it as renderer/runtime preview behavior. Do not
  treat this template as authorizing storage, provider calls, trust state, or
  backend semantics.

